  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When debugging a failed transaction, the code jumps seemingly randomly.  For instance, it jumps from a function call to a line at the end of an uninvolved function in a different contract.  I don't know assembly well enough to verify that the line highlighted in the code window is in fact where the jump landed, but I can verify that it was a very large jump (01764->11223) when the actual function that should be called appears 20 lines above it in the same contract.  It also seems to jump at times when no function is being called, such as when creating a new dynamic array.  \r\n\r\nI'm using 0.5.17+commit.d19bba13.  \r\n\r\nIs this a known issue?  If not, I can put some thought into how to create an example of it.",
