    "body": "Update:\r\nSome of the issue was caused by me replaying a deployment transaction under the assumption that it would reflect changes in the compiled code (which I figured out it doesn't when I noticed that the bytecode is hardcoded in the replay json).  After fixing that, I'm still left with some jumping, but since the code continues to proceed roughly the way I would expect, I'm guessing it's a visual artifact of the debugger.  I also notice that the function stack and locals are frozen at some early point in the code execution and don't update after that.  It seems to be struggling with stepping through/highlighting the code in other source files, but the functions stack and locals stay frozen even after it returns to the main source file.",
